name: LN Fortunate Coffee - Kapal
address: Jl. Raya Kapal No.43, Kapal, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1:
Amazing place! I wish to try all their food! I took kebab and it was just more than amazing! And green soy drink is a bit weird, but as long as a love strange tastes, I like it! I also took fried potato - casava. That's also was great!
The prices are cheap for the food the offer. Atmosphere is nice. Service amazing. I would highly recommend this place! Make sure to check their second floor with an exhibition of dolls in national costumesüòçüôè
Thank you!
review 2: One of the truly heartfelt beautiful food experiences I have enjoyed twice in a row. I visited LN Fortunate Coffee - Kapal with a friend and our guide in October 2023 and was humbled by the staff‚Äôs love, cheer and culinary finesse. Then again on 6th march 2024 I returned to LN Fortunate Coffee - Kapal with a group of 19 and the whole group was enveloped in the joy and wellness spell that this little cafe exudes. Thankyou LN Fortunate Coffee - Kapal, for your excellent food and lively loving spirit. We will be back again.
review 3:
it‚Äôs really one of the best vegan restaurant. The food are delicous and also the ambience really great. One thing that i love the most is their special tea, based on their recipe. It was warm, comforting and healthy.

It‚Äôs hard to find a place with a good tea, and this place offer the great tea to enjoy.

They also give us welcome drink and Kuaci. I think this is very great
review 4: One of best plant-based restaurant I found in Bali, ALLIUM FREE, MSG FREE, no baking soda and baking powder as well. Everything still tastes AMAZING without those ingredients. They also don't use analogue meat which made of gluten. I love their Indonesian menu, terang bulan, otak-otak; their siomay is also great
review 5:
Great place, good food, friendly staff and manager, the price is reasonable even lower compare to what we eat. It‚Äôs totally worth to be back again.
They have different special menu every day. This restaurant also have an awesome charity program. You can also visit the urban garden upstairs, lovely places and must visit!!! The most important is all are vegan! Good for your body, soul and nature!
I recommend the curry noodles coz in my opinion is the best!

name: Sate Babi Bu Ison
address: Kapal, Mengwi, Badung Regency, Bali, Indonesia
review 1:
Another Balinese street food pork satay that's popular among the locals and worth trying.

The Satay is fresh and daily made and grilled directly upon order so we can taste the juicy pork meat.

One portion of nine satays (without the lontong) is 15K.
review 2: I swear this is the best Sate Babi in Bali! Its worth the drive out there if you stay far away. Even for takeaway, its still goooooooood.
review 3: Delicious pork satay in Bali with cheap price, probably IDR 10k for 6 skewers. Although the meat is small, but the taste is much better than the other famous pork satay in Kuta area. The tipat is also soft and delicious. Definitely must try!
review 4: Cheap and very nice pork satay. Small stall on the corner of the street. Nice to have while you on the go.
